<td valign="top" class="postbody">
<hr />
You know, I'm honestly not sure what causes it but you are correct about them disappearing fast.  I have a horrible time keeping up with all the changes to these groups...I'm sure there are lots of dead links on this site's link page (I should probably make it a point to go through and check all of them again).  
<br />

<br />
I do know a lot of people get frustrated about a lack of hits/popularity, so maybe that's part of it.  No one seems to want to wait it out - hits and popularity come with time.  Sure, I get a decent amount of traffic here now, but the first year was horrible!  All the work that goes into a big site might be a turn off too.  Between maintenance and e-mail, I usually put in a couple hours a day working on the site.  Some people don't want to dedicate that much time, and eventually the site goes away (look at my blog - I gave up on it due to a lack of time).  But I ENJOY working on this site, so a couple hours a day is totally worth it!  Plus, I get to meet all you cool people as a result!  I really have met some great people through the site and ghost hunting/cemetery trips     <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="Very Happy" border="0" /></td>
