<td valign="top" class="postbody">
<hr />
Good point, I never thought about the free sites.  But you're right, they're always the ones that disappear super fast.
<br />

<br />
My very first site was on geocities.  I wish I had some screen shots of it...it was absolutely terrible.  I didn't know anything about starting a webpage, and I used their Page Builder app.  It created so much junk code!  
<br />

<br />
After that, I started my frog page using the free web space that came with my ISP.  I think I had a whole 15MB!  It didn't take long before the site outgrew that space, so I decided to look into finding a better host.  I remember I was so nervous about it...looking back, I'm really not sure why!  It really wasn't hard to set up at all - all the hosting sites and domain name sites have great instructions for getting things set up.  
<br />

<br />
My big advice to someone looking for a host?  Make sure you do a search on the company and read user reviews.  The first host I picked was recommended by a coworker, but it was HORRIBLE.  The site was down more than it was up, they made tons of billing mistakes, and their tech support NEVER responded (which was funny since they claimed to have 24/7 support).  I was constantly frustrated.  I did a search on their name, and I found countless bad reviews...in fact, I think I only found one good review online!  I wish I would have done that before I chose them as my host.  Needless to say, I cancelled my service with them as soon as the contract was up!  My current host is a million times better.
<br />

<br />
And Brian, I can't wait to check out your new sites!   <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="Very Happy" border="0" />   Are you still going to have a separate site for the cemetery photos?</td>
</tr>
